{
  "answer": "**The verse work is *Elene* by Cynewulf, Chapter 1.**[^1]\n\nThe poem opens by setting the scene during Constantine's reign, with a hostile alliance mustering by the Danube: \"The Hunnish people and Hrethgoths hardened, / Franks and Hugas, a fearsome force, / had mustered their might by the river’s margin, / on Danube’s dark bank...\"[^2]\n\nConstantine, encamped there, then dreams of a heavenly herald revealing a radiant, gem-adorned cross (described as \"gleaming with gold, with gems adorned, / a beacon of brightest wood, brilliantly shining\"), on which appear \"letters of light... a radiant message\": **\"By this sign, conquer.\"**[^3][^4]\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [Chapter 1](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/).\n[^2]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [Chapter 1](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-14a3be).\n[^3]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [Chapter 1](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-acdc07).\n[^4]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [Chapter 1](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-306e06).",
